frontends: const-ify unidir_accel ctl_table proc_handler for kernel 6.12

14.0.r8's ecm_front_end_unidir_accel_proc_handler (added in 78265ae) was
missed by the a52268c ECM_CTL_TABLE_CONST sweep and kept the old non-const
ctl_table + __user buffer signature. Kernel 6.12 makes the proc_handler
ctl_table const, so match the other handlers in this file.

Signed-off-by: Julius Bairaktaris <julius@bairaktaris.de>

--- a/frontends/ecm_front_end_common.c
+++ b/frontends/ecm_front_end_common.c
@@ -1357,7 +1357,7 @@ static int ecm_front_end_tcp_denied_port
  * ecm_front_end_unidir_accel_proc_handler()
  *	Per-direction acceleration sysctl handler.
  */
-int ecm_front_end_unidir_accel_proc_handler(struct ctl_table *ctl, int write, void __user *buffer, size_t *lenp, loff_t *ppos)
+int ecm_front_end_unidir_accel_proc_handler(ECM_CTL_TABLE_CONST struct ctl_table *ctl, int write, void *buffer, size_t *lenp, loff_t *ppos)
 {
 	int ret;
 
